trans-unit.source: Frequently Asked Questions
trans-unit.target: Frequently Asked Questions

trans-unit.source: Why would I choose Visual Studio “Preview”?
trans-unit.target: Why would I choose Visual Studio “Preview”?

trans-unit.source: If you are a Visual Studio enthusiast you'll want to get your hands on the latest pre-release Visual Studio Preview that contains innovations, bug fixes, and platform support not yet in Visual Studio.
trans-unit.target: If you are a Visual Studio enthusiast you'll want to get your hands on the latest pre-release Visual Studio Preview that contains innovations, bug fixes, and platform support not yet in Visual Studio.

trans-unit.source: Your feedback will help ensure we release only the best.
trans-unit.target: Your feedback will help ensure we release only the best.

trans-unit.source: All new tools and platform support will be first released to “Preview”.
trans-unit.target: All new tools and platform support will be first released to “Preview”.

trans-unit.source: Check out the release rhythm to learn about the overall release model.
trans-unit.target: Check out the release rhythm to learn about the overall release model.

trans-unit.source: Can I install both Visual Studio and Visual Studio “Preview” on the same machine?
trans-unit.target: Can I install both Visual Studio and Visual Studio “Preview” on the same machine?

trans-unit.source: Yes, Visual Studio and Visual Studio “Preview” can be installed side-by-side on the same device.
trans-unit.target: Yes, Visual Studio and Visual Studio “Preview” can be installed side-by-side on the same device.

trans-unit.source: If you are using extensions, you will need to reinstall them for each instance of Visual Studio.
trans-unit.target: If you are using extensions, you will need to reinstall them for each instance of Visual Studio.

trans-unit.source: Note that installing both will not double the size of your Visual Studio installation because some components are shared between the two.
trans-unit.target: Note that installing both will not double the size of your Visual Studio installation because some components are shared between the two.

trans-unit.source: For example, if you install the Windows SDK for both instances, the Windows SDK will be installed only once on your computer.
trans-unit.target: For example, if you install the Windows SDK for both instances, the Windows SDK will be installed only once on your computer.

trans-unit.source: May I build production apps?
trans-unit.target: May I build production apps?

trans-unit.source: No, “Preview” is not licensed to build shipping apps.
trans-unit.target: No, “Preview” is not licensed to build shipping apps.

trans-unit.source: Like any other pre-releases of Visual Studio, it is not supported in production environments.
trans-unit.target: Like any other pre-releases of Visual Studio, it is not supported in production environments.

trans-unit.source: You should install the release version for use in Production environments which you can find here: Downloads
trans-unit.target: You should install the release version for use in Production environments which you can find here: Downloads

trans-unit.source: How do I report problems or suggestions on “Preview”?
trans-unit.target: How do I report problems or suggestions on “Preview”?

trans-unit.source: To report bugs for any instance of Visual Studio, use “Report a Problem” from the Help menu in Visual Studio.
trans-unit.target: To report bugs for any instance of Visual Studio, use “Report a Problem” from the Help menu in Visual Studio.

trans-unit.source: The Visual Studio team will automatically see that you’re using “Preview”.
trans-unit.target: The Visual Studio team will automatically see that you’re using “Preview”.

trans-unit.source: To submit product feature or experience suggestions, use “Provide a suggestion” from the Help menu.
trans-unit.target: To submit product feature or experience suggestions, use “Provide a suggestion” from the Help menu.

trans-unit.source: Is Visual Studio “Preview” supported?
trans-unit.target: Is Visual Studio “Preview” supported?

trans-unit.source: Visual Studio “Preview” is designed for you to get an early look at upcoming features and changes, and to provide feedback on those changes.
trans-unit.target: Visual Studio “Preview” is designed for you to get an early look at upcoming features and changes, and to provide feedback on those changes.

trans-unit.source: While, Visual Studio “Preview” is not covered by Microsoft Technical Support, we encourage you to submit your feedback via Report-a-Problem, and we’ll make every effort to respond to that feedback.
trans-unit.target: While, Visual Studio “Preview” is not covered by Microsoft Technical Support, we encourage you to submit your feedback via Report-a-Problem, and we’ll make every effort to respond to that feedback.

trans-unit.source: I no longer want to use “Preview.” How do I remove it?
trans-unit.target: I no longer want to use “Preview.” How do I remove it?

trans-unit.source: If you no longer want to participate in “Preview”, you can use the Visual Studio Installer to remove it.
trans-unit.target: If you no longer want to participate in “Preview”, you can use the Visual Studio Installer to remove it.

trans-unit.source: Once you have the installer open, uninstall any instances of “Preview” by clicking on the installation menu and chose "Uninstall".
trans-unit.target: Once you have the installer open, uninstall any instances of “Preview” by clicking on the installation menu and chose "Uninstall".

trans-unit.source: In case you have Visual Studio IDE installed side-by-side, we recommend running "Repair" on your other installation as a precaution.
trans-unit.target: In case you have Visual Studio IDE installed side-by-side, we recommend running "Repair" on your other installation as a precaution.

trans-unit.source: For more information, please see our Release Notes.
trans-unit.target: For more information, please see our Release Notes.

trans-unit.source: How do I install the latest released version of Visual Studio?
trans-unit.target: How do I install the latest released version of Visual Studio?

trans-unit.source: To install the release (go-live) version of Visual Studio 2017, visit: Downloads.
trans-unit.target: To install the release (go-live) version of Visual Studio 2017, visit: Downloads.

trans-unit.source: Which edition of Visual Studio “Preview” should I install?
trans-unit.target: Which edition of Visual Studio “Preview” should I install?

trans-unit.source: We strongly recommend that you choose the same edition that you currently have a license for.
trans-unit.target: We strongly recommend that you choose the same edition that you currently have a license for.

trans-unit.source: If you do not have an existing license, then you should consider using Community after reading the License Terms.
trans-unit.target: If you do not have an existing license, then you should consider using Community after reading the License Terms.

trans-unit.source: If you have a Professional or Enterprise license already for Visual Studio, then you should choose the edition that corresponds to your license when downloading Preview.
trans-unit.target: If you have a Professional or Enterprise license already for Visual Studio, then you should choose the edition that corresponds to your license when downloading Preview.
